{"id":11377,"date":"2013-01-16T15:40:27","date_gmt":"2013-01-16T20:40:27","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=11377"},"modified":"2023-04-24T16:29:47","modified_gmt":"2023-04-24T12:29:47","slug":"tested-akhirah-yawm-al-qiyamah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/16\/tested-akhirah-yawm-al-qiyamah\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Hereafter: Some people tested on Judgment Day"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Aswad ibn Sari\u2019 reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<b>There are four kinds of people on the Day of Resurrection: a deaf man who cannot hear anything, a mad man, a senile man, and a man who died in the period before Islam. The deaf man will say: O Lord, Islam came and I could not hear anything. The mad man will say: O Lord, Islam came and the children threw filth at me. The senile man will say: O Lord, Islam came and I could not understand anything. The man who died before Islam will say: O Lord, there was no messenger from You who came to me. Allah will make them promise to obey Him. Then, He will command them to enter the fire<\/b>.<b> By the one in whose hand is the soul of Muhammad, if they enter the fire, it will become cool and peaceful<\/b>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 16301<\/p>\n<p>Grade:\u00a0<i>Hasan <\/i>(fair) according to Al-Arna&#8217;ut<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0648\u064e\u062f\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0633\u064e\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0639\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0646\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0631\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0629\u064c \u064a